Description:
$800 a weekInternshipStudyportals, the global education choice platform, is looking for a dedicated, creative and hands-on intern to support our Boston team!
During your 6 months internship, you will be working very closely with the entire team as well as the COO North America. You have the chance to be involved into a broad range of marketing and business administration actives (mostly B2B).
We strongly encourage interns to bring in their own ideas and suggestions; you will also get the opportunity to have an impact on current projects together with a highly motivated, international team!
Your profile:
Currently enrolled in a Bachelor or Master’s degree program (ideally in the field of Business Development, Marketing/Communications, Event planning and/or Entrepreneurship);
A positive, self-motivated individual with a high level of enthusiasm and willingness to learn;
Goal-oriented and social media savvy;
Outgoing, enthusiastic and creative;
Achieving a GPA of 2.5 or better.
Requirements
Analytical thinking and great attention to detail;
Excellent verbal and written English skills
Strong computer skills (Microsoft Office, Google Docs, Adobe Photoshop);
Excellent communication skills (verbally & written);
Result-oriented working style;
Passion for Branding and Brand Management;
Critical thinking;
Firsthand experience with Google Analytics & Google AdWords is a plus;
Highly organized;
Being enrolled in an American University during the entire duration of the internship is a must.
Responsibilities:
Conference organization;
Support the team creating newsletters, e-mail campaigns, online promotions, etc.;
Provide support to social media efforts to target new audiences;
Research and analyze competitor marketing and sales materials;
Prepare presentations for management and clients;
Sales support: research relevant contact information about partners, organizations and opinion leaders (journalists);
Business Administration: Help with tasks in HR and recruiting, after-sales and administration (get to learn how a business operates from A-Z).
Benefits
Professional Skill Development and Resume Building workshops;
A full-time internship position starting as soon as possible, for at least 6 months;
The opportunity to work with highly dedicated colleagues from 36 different nationalities;
Possibilities for internship extension or promotion;
Letters of Recommendation and monthly one-on-one mentoring sessions with your manager;
Involvement with one of the fastest growing start-ups in the higher education industry;
The opportunity to make our world a little bit better and be at the core of the growth phase of a study choice giant, that the world market was waiting for.
A compensation (stipent) of $ 800/months
Studyportals will make reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with known disabilities, in accordance with applicable law.
